{"_id":"3DNp4ei2LueeZtu0","name":"(C) Hard Knocks","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Sometimes luck is just hard-earned experience. Your crew starts each job with +1 gambit.","class":"Cerberus","price":"2","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/scout-ship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5QVY0GEadcKTaGNF","name":"(F) Black Market Contacts","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Able to get you all the modules (even illegal ones) your ship needs, even when you're wanted. Resourceful. Mobile. Illegal modules (as usual) may require you to run a job to acquire them. Your contact may know where to find them, and give you a leg up, but it's up to you to get things that just aren't available at any price (prototypes, rare devices, and incredibly illegal things like coherence cannons).","class":"Firedrake","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/starfighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9QxU8Z7G1eT8XKA1","name":"(S) Dark Hyperspace Lane Maps","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"These are routes through systems that aren't officially maintained. Sometimes they are faster. They are always less patrolled. Often they are full of Way creatures, pirates, and other scoundrels. The ride is never as smooth as it is along the Starsmith-maintained routes. You don't want to think too hard about the poor fools that died or got lost forever mapping these routes.","class":"Stardancer","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/spaceship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"A6SqTg0EIrAA5hLJ","name":"(C) Tracers","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"A wide array of ways to track your targets. Includes tiny bugs that can be hidden on clothes with a suave pat on the back, beacons that can attach to hulls, and even transmission cloners for comms. Legality varies (often by the importance of the target), but a license makes it all legal.","class":"Cerberus","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/scout-ship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Ei0RyyEKxXOxolV9","name":"(F) Way Blessed","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Some people are just plain lucky. The common folk think this is some sort of sign. Don't look too much into it. You start with +1 gambit at the start of every job.","class":"Firedrake","price":"2","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/starfighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"L5znCJ4829WZgqmx","name":"(F) Secret Base","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Could be inside ancient Ur ruins on a planet. Maybe buildings inside a massive asteroid. Possibly an old and forgotten station, long abandoned but now repurposed. You have found and commissioned a hiding spot away from the baleful gaze of the Hegemony where you and your allies can meet, hide, lick your wounds, and plan your jobs, all without the Hegemony finding out. It's secret...for now.","class":"Firedrake","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/starfighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OClA4KdnedLnxIR1","name":"(C) Stun Weapons","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"A wide variety of weapons for capturing and securing prisoners without (serious) harm. Includes, but is not limited to:\nRestraints. [0 load]\nStun batons. [1 load]\nStun settings on blasters. Not the heavy kind. [1 load]\nStun grenades. Replaces detonator on the sheet. [1 load]\nKnockout drugs. May not work on some xenos. [0 load]\nNot required to bring on jobs, but useful if you want to claim bounties. Generally legal.","class":"Cerberus","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/scout-ship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XXo0x3ir0pXwMMQV","name":"(F) Popular Support","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"It takes work to win hearts and minds, but your cause has supporters among the common folk. When you approach a planet or a station, ask the GM who there might be a sympathizer. This may make escapes (and simply walking around while wanted) much easier.","class":"Firedrake","price":"3","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/starfighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aoGqh17UKJ0EKQjR","name":"(S) Smuggler's Rigging","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Webbing or fake skin used to hold small items close to the body and a great way to sneak them past security. Adds some hands-free carry room while working on the outside of the ship, and lets you smuggle a blaster into a well guarded meeting while keeping the stylish cut of your coat. You can only carry/hide one item of a max of 1 load this way.","class":"Stardancer","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/spaceship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"h43IkhLX7d9vCtPm","name":"(C) Personal Vehicles","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Your crew has a few (perhaps one per crew member) sleek single-seater craft that can fold up tight enough to fit into a reasonable parking space. Limited fuel, but can break atmo. Can carry basic weapons, though they can't seriously damage anything freighter-sized or larger. You may want a landing bay on your ship.","class":"Cerberus","price":"2","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/scout-ship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hYFxpz2tUZcZtaC4","name":"(S) Thrillseekers","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Each PC gets +1 stress box (increase stress max to 10).","class":"Stardancer","price":"3","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/spaceship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"m683MKG6SdAMidWO","name":"(S) False Ship Papers","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Every smuggler needs a few wellforged documents, giving the crew and ship identities that are less wanted in any given system. These papers often simplify gate travel if the transponder and ship match. You have a couple different sets you can swap between, even if you do have to practice responding to a new name at every checkpoint. May make following and tracking you more difficult by enemy factions.","class":"Stardancer","price":"1","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/spaceship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"tXGdoxkMGfpZ6a5t","name":"(F) Driven","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Each PC gets +1 trauma box. This can bring a PC with 4 trauma back into play if you wish.","class":"Firedrake","price":"3","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/starfighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wJZQAjm52nOMwpxu","name":"(C) Smooth Criminals","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Sometimes legality is only a question of who has the gun. Each crew member gains +1 stress box (total 10).","class":"Cerberus","price":"3","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/scout-ship.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"zmp4D2rTlvHOvpKj","name":"(S) Lucky Charm","permission":{"default":0},"type":"crew_upgrade","data":{"description":"Whether an Ur artifact or a few mementos prominently displayed on the bridge, sometimes luck is just about believing in something. The crew starts with +1 gambit every job.","class":"Stardancer","price":"2","logic":"","crew_type":"undefined"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/spaceship.png","effects":[]}
